    "processing capabilities of the human brain, which excels in handling complex and uncertain data, and surpasses machines in decisionmaking with large, heterogeneous datasets.",
    "OI is built on key technological advancements, including the groundbreaking induction of pluripotent stem cells (iPSC) from human somatic cells and the subsequent development of 3D brain organoids from these iPSCs.",
    "These advancements in 3D organoid culture have led to more physiologically accurate and scalable models for brain functions.",
    "Additionally, microfluidic perfusion systems are being developed to substitute for vasculature in brain organoids, providing essential nutrients and removing waste, critical for maintaining organoid homeostasis and viability.",
    "Another vital component is the incorporation of 3D microelectrode arrays for recording electrophysiological outputs from brain organoids, enabling the exploration of their computational potential and learning mechanisms."
